You go out and spend how ever much time (and more then likely zero to very little plat) to get those 6 items. Lets say that all together it takes you oh, one day played time if it is a very hard quest. Now there is that last step, the grandmaster tailerer. Now, in order to BE a grandmaster tailerer you need what...over 200kpp, and weeks of played time? If you are lucky? K lets sum this up.<br>
<br>
Person1 spends 0 plat and a day to get 6 components. <br>
<br>
Person2 spends weeks and over 200kpp to get the skill.<br>
<br>
Person1 offers Person2 200pp to do their part in making this 50kpp item. <br>
<br>
person2 says screw you if you want to be fair 48kpp of that item would rightfully be mine but at least offer me a reasonable compensation for my time and plat. Lets say maybe 5kpp instead of 200pp for a 50kpp item? As a minimum?<br>
