<br>
When I make armor to sell, or make armor for other people, I know exactly how much it costs me to buy the components necessary, and therefore know how much the item should be sold for.  Personally, I price the stuff I make at exactly twice the cost to buy the raw materials and do the combines, taking into account failure rates for all steps.  <br>
<br>
If someone wants me to make them something that they can and probably eventually will sell, I will demand the full cost of the components along with the components to combine, or if the components cannot be priced or failure rates estimated, half the current market value of the item.  That way if they do sell it, we both end up with half the profit.<br>
